==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Photo-electric cell
<hw>Photo-electric cell</hw>. <def>A cell (as one of two electrodes
embedded in selenium) which by exposure to light generates an electric
current.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Photo-electricity</ent>⟦br⟧
